returns.para:
n: The minimum filter order that meets the design requirements;
            wn: Normalized cutoff frequency, range is [0,1], where 1 corresponds to the Nyquist frequency fs/2;
            beta: The shape factor of the Kaiser window, used to control the main lobe width and side lobe attenuation of the window function;
            bandType: FIR filter band type.

n: The minimum filter order that meets the design requirements;
            wn: Normalized cutoff frequency, range is [0,1], where 1 corresponds to the Nyquist frequency fs/2;
            amplitudes: The amplitude response at each frequency point;
            weights: The weights for each frequency band, with a length equal to half of the number of bands(bands/2).
